@NODE Voraus " MEExchange needs"

	MEExchange needs:
	- OS 3.0+
	- the WBStart.library ((c) by Stefan Becker)
	  in the Aminet under: util/libs/
	  (is included)

	MEExchange only testet on a AMIGA 500 (OS3.0, 9MB Ram, 68020, 520MD HD).

@ENDNODE
	
@NODE Was " What do MEExchange?"

	MEExchange is a replacement for the org. Exchange-Prg.,
	but with some new functions:
	
	- a small commodity-managmet-function, e.g. you can
	  start and managment your Commodities
	- the posibility to de/aktivit and quit the Commodties
	- ARexx-Port

@ENDNODE

@NODE install " Installation"

	The installaion is easy, you must only use the
	Installer-Script.

@ENDNODE

@NODE start " Start"

	The start from the Workbench:
	Dopple-Click on the programm-icon.
	The standart toolypes are supportet:
	CX_POPKEY, CX_POPUP, CX_PRIORITY,
	 Standart is:
	 lalt control help, NO, 0

	At the start from the CLU/Shell you can give the same
	Parameter, like that:
	
	 MEExchange H="alt e" P R=1
	 
	 with:
	 H=Hotkey: Hotkey/Popkey-combination
	 P=Popup: if it there themainwindow will open
	 R=Priority: say with which Priority MEExchange runs

	If there no parameter the icon will read.

@ENDNODE

@NODE bedienung " Using"

	The using of MEExchange is easy and self explained,
	but:
	
	- @{" Mainwindow  " LINK "haupt"}
	- @{" Listwindow  " LINK "liste"}
	- @{" Prefswindow " LINK "prefs"}

	All windows can open and use to the same time, you can
	switch between them with the TAB-Key.

@ENDNODE

@NODE haupt " Using Hauptfenster"

	You can close (hide) the window with the Close-Button, the
	menu-point Hide or the ESC-Key.

	Commodities:
	 list all running commoditie, on a double-click on the commoditie
	 MEExchange will open the window of this commoditie (if the
	 commoditie have one)

		You can move the List with the keys:
		- Cursor up
		- Cursor down
		- Shift+Cursor up: To the begin of the list
		- Shift+Cursor down: To the end of the list

	Or:
		You use a Mouse with Wheel and a program to
		handle it.

	Deaktivate all:
	 deaktivate all running commoditie

	Aktivate all:
	 aktivate all running commoditie

	Remove all:
	 remove all running commodtie (but MEExchange ask >Realy?< befor)

	Remove:
	 remove the selectet commoditie

	Aktiv:
	 aktivate/deaktivate the selectet commoditie

	Show:
	 show the window from the selectet window (if the commodtie
	 have one)

	Hide:
	 close from the selectet commoditie the window (if it was open)

@ENDNODE

@NODE liste " Using Liste"

	Here you can managment your Commodities, this means
	you can start (Liste window), stop and handle (Main window)
	your Commodities from one point:

		MEExchange.

	List:
	 all (with new) createt commodity,
	 with an double-click you select/deselect the entry,
	 it will marked with the # at the begin 

		You can move the List with the keys:
		- Cursor up
		- Cursor down
		- Shift+Cursor up: To the begin of the list
		- Shift+Cursor down: To the end of the list

	Or:
		You use a Mouse with Wheel and a program
		to handle it.

	Remove:
	 remove the selected entry
	
	New:
	 create a new entry in the list
	 
	Sort:
	 sort the List
	 
	Start:
	 start the select commoditie
	
	Start all:
	 start all commodities in the list
	
	Start sel.:
	 start all with # markt entrys
	
	Save:
	 save the list and close the window
	
	Use:
	 use the list and close the window
	
	Cancel:
	 remove the changes in the list and close the window

@ENDNODE


@NODE Prefs " Prefs"

	Here you can change the Tooltypes to the runtime of the
	program. If you close the window with the Save or Use-Button
	the changes will be direct done. By Save the Tooltypes in
	the Icon will be changed.

@ENDNODE

@NODE ARexx " ARexx"

	MEExchange has a ARexx-Port with name "MEEXCHANGE.REXX",
	you can use this commands:

	- ? or HELP
		shows all commands of the ARexx-Port
			
	- QUIT
		Quit MEExchange

	- ENABLE <Name of the Commodity> <ALL>
		aktivate the commodity, if you use the option all then
		you aktivate all commoditys

	- DISABLE <Name of the Commodity> <ALL>
		deaktivate one (or all) commoditys

	- REMOVE <Name of the Commodity> <ALL>
		remove one (or all) commoditys

	- HIDE <Name of the Commodity> <ALL>
		close the (or all) commodity-window

	- SHOW <Name of the Commodity>
		shows the (or all) commodity-window

	- LIST
		list all running commodity
	
	- LISTC
		list all commoditys from the managment-list
	
	- START <Name> <ALL> <SEL>
		start the (or the sellect or all) commodity form
		the managment-list

	If you give no Name of the Commodity by Hide, Show, Enabele,
	Disable and Remove the program use as Name his own name (Exchange).


	Here a Sample-Script:

	/*
		 ARexx-Sample-Script for MEExchange
	*/

	OPTIONS RESULTS
	ADDRESS MEEXCHANGE.REXX

	SAY "Which command?"
	DO FOREVER
	 Options PROMPT "My Choise: "
	 PULL command
	 if command="" then
	  Break
	 Else
	  command
	  say result
	 end
	ENDE

@ENDNODE

@NODE zukunft " Version/Future"

	Version 1.0:
	- The program works
	
	Version 1.1:
	- The bug in the GUI is fixed
	- The bug in message-handling is fixed
	- the CLI/Shell-start can now handel parameters
	- Asynchron Window-Handling
	- More AREXX-Commads
	- A better Guide

	Version 1.1b:
	- The Infotext is now correct cleard
	
	Version 1.2:
	- The bug at the remove a liste-item is removed
	- The GUI is a bit changed.
	- The Message-Handling is improved

	Version 1.3: (28.07.1998)
	- the windows open now in the middle of the screen
	- a bug in the ARexx-Port is removed
	- The ListGadgets can now moved with the keypad
	- a bug in the Locale support is removed
	- The Message-Handling is improved
	- A better Guide

	Version 2.0: (15.11.1998)
	- The Message-Handling is improved
	- You can change the Tooltypes now in the Program

	Version 2.1: (15.12.1998)
	- The menus are now NewLook like
	- The program is faster, and a liltle bit smaller

	Version 2.2: (09.01.1999)
	- The bug in the prefs is removed, cancel, cancel now realy	

	Version 3.0: (19.06.1999)
	- Now is the onlinehelp asyncron
	- Some Enforcer-Hits are removed
	- The bug in the commodity-managmet is removed
	- Some locale support errors are removed

	Future:
